# Read-only: computes and returns the polygon waypoints around the
# standoff pose (see TrajectoryPlanner::polygonWaypointsAroundStandoff)
# WITHOUT moving the arm. Lets a caller (e.g. calibration_broadcaster_node)
# drive the waypoints itself one at a time via TracePath.srv, sampling
# between moves, without duplicating trajectory_planner's standoff/polygon
# geometry math or config (camera_frame, standoff_m, facing_rpy_rad,
# polygon_num_corners, polygon_radius_m all stay owned by trajectory_planner).
---
bool success
string message
geometry_msgs/Pose[] waypoints
# The center pose the waypoints were generated around (the arm's own
# current pose at call time — see polygonWaypointsAroundStandoff's doc
# comment, 2026-07-22 redesign: no longer the camera's TF-derived
# standoff pose). Added so a caller (calibration_broadcaster_node's
# random-pose sampling phase) can generate its own additional offset
# poses from the SAME center the polygon corners used, without a second
# "get current pose" round-trip or duplicating this node's own
# MoveGroupInterface/TF access.
geometry_msgs/Pose center_pose